INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3400','letter','1784-07-06','On board ship Active','','','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I have been sixteen days at sea, and have not attempted to write a single letter. \'T is true, I have kept a journal whenever I was able ; but that must be close locked up, unless I was sure to hand it you with safety.','ltr_aba3400.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3401','letter','1784-09-05','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','Auteuil is a village four miles distant from Paris, and one from Passy. The house we have taken is large, commodious, and agreeably situated, near the Woods of Boulogne, which belong to the King, and which Mr. Adams calls his park','ltr_aba3401.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3402','letter','1784-09-05','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','I promised to write to you from the Hague, but your uncle\'s unexpected arrival at London prevented me. Your uncle purchased an excellent travelling coach in London, and hired a post-chaise for our servants.','ltr_aba3402.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3403','letter','1784-12-09','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I go into Paris sometimes to the plays, of which I am very fond ; but I so severely pay for it, that I refrain many times upon account of my health. It never fails giving me a severe headache','ltr_aba3403.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3404','letter','1784-12-14','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','From the interest you take in every thing which concerns your friends, I hear you inquiring how I do, how I live, whom I see, where I visit, who visit me.','ltr_aba3404.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3405','letter','1785-01-18','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','John','Shaw','','individual','','Amongst the public edifices which are worthy of notice in this country, are several churches. I went, a few days since, to see three of the most celebrated in Paris.','ltr_aba3405.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3406','letter','1785-01-20','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','','Storer','','Those only, who have crossed the ocean, can realize the pleasure which is felt at the sight of land. The inexperienced traveller is more sensible of this, than those who frequently traverse the ocean.','','description','ltr_aba3406.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3407','letter','1785-01-24','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','And in the first place, my dear Lucy, shall I find a little fault with you ? A fault, from which neither your good sister, nor cousin Abby, is free. It is that all of you so much neglect your handwriting.','ltr_aba3407.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3408','letter','1785-02-20','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I have seen many of the beauties, and some of the deformities, of this old world. I have been more than ever convinced, that there is no summit of virtue, and no depth of vice, which human nature is not capable of rising to, on the one hand, or sinking into, on the other.','ltr_aba3408.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3409','letter','1785-05-07','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','Well, my dear niece, I have returned from Mr. Adams\'s. When I got there, I found a pretty large company. It consisted of the Marquis and Madame de la Fayette...','ltr_aba3409.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3410','letter','1785-05-08','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','You can hardly form an idea how difficult and expensive it is to be housekeeping a few months at a time in so many different countries. It has been Mr. Adams\'s fortune, ever since he came abroad, not to live a year at a time in one place.','ltr_aba3410.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3411','letter','1785-05-08','Auteuil','','FRA','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','Can my dear sister realize that it is near eleven months since I left her ? To me it seems incredible ; more like a dream than a reality. Yet it ought to appear the longest ten months of my life','ltr_aba3411.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3412','letter','1785-06-24','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','The sitting of Parliament, the birth-day of the King, and the famous celebration of the music of Handel at Westminster Abbey had drawn together such a concourse of people, that we were glad to get into lodgings at the moderate price of a guinea per day','ltr_aba3412.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3413','letter','1785-08-15','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','It is one of the finest squares in London. The air is as pure as it can be so near a great city. It is but a small distance from Hyde Park, round which I sometimes walk, but oftener ride.','ltr_aba3413.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3414','letter','1785-08-27','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','It is usual at a large entertainment, to bring the solid food in the first course. The second consists of lighter diet, kickshaws, trifles, whip syllabub, &c. ; the third is the dessert, consisting of the fruits of the season, and sometimes foreign sweetmeats.','ltr_aba3414.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3415','letter','1785-09-06','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','John Quincy','Adams','','individual','','The chocolate grew cold, the top of the tea-pot was forgotten, and the bread and butter went down uneaten. Yet nobody felt the loss of breakfast. So near akin are joy and grief, that the effect is often similar.','ltr_aba3415.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3416','letter','1785-09-30','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','With these ideas, you may be sure my countenance will never wear that suppliant appearance, which begs for notice. Consequently, I never expect to be a Court favorite.','ltr_aba3416.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3417','letter','1785-10-01','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','You must know that yesterday the whole diplomatic corps dined here ; that is, his Lordship the Marquis of Carmarthen, and all the foreign ministers, fifteen in all, and to-day the newspapers proclaim it.','ltr_aba3417.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3418','letter','1786-03-04','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','I seldom feel a sufficient stimulus for writing until I hear that a vessel is just about to sail, and then I find myself so deep in debt, that I know not where to begin to discharge the account ; but it is time for me to be a little more provident','ltr_aba3418.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3419','letter','1786-04-02','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','The social affections are and may be made the truest channels for our pleasures and comforts to flow through. Heaven formed us not for ourselves but others','ltr_aba3419.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3420','letter','1786-04-06','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','When a body has attended one of these parties, you know the whole of the entertainment. There were about two hundred persons present last evening. Three large rooms full of card-tables','ltr_aba3420.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3421','letter','1786-05-21','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I thank you most sincerely for all your kindness to my dear sons, and hope they will ever bear a grateful remembrance of it ; the account you give of their behaviour and conduct is such as I hope they merit.','ltr_aba3421.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3422','letter','1786-07-20','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','the other day a gentleman presented me with a card to go and see the corpse of the Duke of Northumberland, who died at his house in the country, but was brought here to be laid in state.','ltr_aba3422.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3423','letter','1786-09-12','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','By the last vessels, I wrote some of my friends that I was going to visit Holland. That I had a desire to see that country you will not wonder at','ltr_aba3423.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3424','letter','1786-09-27','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','John Quincy','Adams','','individual','','Since I wrote you last, I have made two excursions, one to Holland, and one of a week to the Hyde, the seat of Mr. Brand-Hollis. Here I was both entertained and delighted.','ltr_aba3424.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3425','letter','1786-11-21','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','This being so wholly groundless, it roused the quick feelings of Mr. Adams, who replied, a little warmly, Give me leave to tell you, Sir, that people who hold this language, betray a total ignorance of the subject.','ltr_aba3425.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3426','letter','1787-01-20','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I will now give you some account of my late tour to Bath, that seat of fashionable resort, where, like the rest of the world, I spent a fortnight in amusement and dissipation, but returned, I assure you, with double pleasure to my own fireside','ltr_aba3426.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3427','letter','1787-02-25','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I think I should not feel more anxious if I was in the midst of all the disturbances, than I do at this distance, where imagination is left at full liberty. When law and justice are laid prostrate, who or what is secure ?','ltr_aba3427.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3428','letter','1787-04-23','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','We have accounts, by way of New York, to the 8th of March, which inform us that General Lincoln had met with more resistance from the insurgents than we had reason to expect from former accounts','ltr_aba3428.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3429','letter','1787-07-16','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','I have had with me for a fortnight a little daughter of Mr. Jefferson\'s, who arrived here with a young negro girl, her servant, from Virginia.','ltr_aba3429.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3430','letter','1787-09-15','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Mary','Cranch','','individual','','When I wrote you last, I was just going to set out on a journey to the West of England. I promised you to visit Mr. Cranch\'s friends and relatives. This we did, as I shall relate to you.','ltr_aba3430.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3431','letter','1787-10-03','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','Lucy','Cranch','','individual','','I have given your mamma and sister some account of my late excursion to Devonshire. We returned home through Bristol, and took Oxford in our way','ltr_aba3431.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3432','letter','1787-10-12','London','','ENG','Abigail','Adams','','John Quincy','Adams','','individual','','I cannot begin my letter by thanking you for yours. You write so seldom that you do not give me the opportunity. Yet I think you would feel disappointed if you did not get a few lines from me.','ltr_aba3432.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3433','letter','1789-09-27','Richmond Hill','NY','US','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','I write to you, my dear sister, not from the disputed banks of the Potomac, the Susquehanna, or the Delaware, but from the peaceful borders of the Hudson ; a situation where the hand of nature has so lavishly displayed her beauties','ltr_aba3433.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3434','letter','1790-09-06','New York','NY','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Brand','','individual','','If my heart had not done you more justice than my pen, I would disown it. I have so long omitted writing to you, that my conscience has been a very severe accuser of me.','ltr_aba3434.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3435','letter','1790-11-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','Bush Hill is a very beautiful place. But the grand and sublime I left at Richmond Hill. The cultivation in sight and prospect are superior, but the Schuylkill is no more like the Hudson, than I to Hercules.','ltr_aba3435.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3436','letter','1790-12-26','Bush Hill','PA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','On Friday evening last, I went with Charles to the drawing-room, being the first of my appearance in public. The room became full before I left it, and the circle very brilliant.','ltr_aba3436.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3437','letter','1791-01-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','I think you do perfectly right in refusing to go into public during the absence of Colonel Smith. The society of a few friends is that from which most pleasure and satisfaction are to be derived.','ltr_aba3437.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3438','letter','1791-01-25','Philadelphia','PA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','You must not flatter yourself with the expectation of hearing from Colonel Smith until the February packet arrives. It is as soon as you ought to think of it.','ltr_aba3438.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3439','letter','1791-02-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','The education of your children will occupy much of your time, and you will always keep in mind the great importance of first principles, and the necessity of instilling the precepts of morality very early into their minds.','ltr_aba3439.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3440','letter','1791-03-20','Bush Hill','PA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','We have had a very severe winter in this State, as you may judge when I tell you that we have consumed forty cords of wood in four months. It has been as cold as any winter we have at the northward.','ltr_aba3440.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3441','letter','1794-02-03','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','I go from home but very little, yet I do not find my time hang heavy upon my hands. You know that I have no aversion to join in the cheerful circle, or mix in the world, when opportunity offers.','ltr_aba3441.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3442','letter','1794-03-08','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','I have been only two davs (when I was too sick to attend) absent from the sick bed of your grandmother. Your desire, that her last days might be rendered as comfortable as it is possible to make them, has been fulfilled. ','ltr_aba3442.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3443','letter','1794-03-10','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','I think our ladies ought to be cautious of foreigners. I am almost led to suspect a spy in every strange character. It is much too easy a matter for a man, if he has property, to get introduced into company in this country','ltr_aba3443.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3444','letter','1797-11-08','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Adams','','individual','','I have much upon my mind which I could say to you ; prudence forbids my committing it to writing.','ltr_aba3444.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3445','letter','1797-02-08','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','John','Adams','','individual','','And may it prove an auspicious prelude to each ensuing season. You have this day to declare yourself head of a nation.','ltr_aba3445.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3446','letter','1797-04-26','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','John','Adams','','individual','','The funeral rites performed, I prepare to set out on the morrow. I long to leave a place, where every scene and object wears a gloom, or looks so to me. My agitated mind wants repose.','ltr_aba3446.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3447','letter','1800-11-13','Washington','MD','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Adams','','individual','','Well, my dear son, South Carolina has behaved as your father always said she would. The consequence to us, personally, is, that we retire from public life.','ltr_aba3447.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3448','letter','1800-11-21','Washington','MD','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','You must keep all this to yourself, and, when asked how I like it, say that I write you the situation is beautiful, which is true. The house is made habitable, but there is not a single apartment finished','ltr_aba3448.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3449','letter','1800-11-27','Washington','MD','US','Abigail','Adams','','Abigail','Smith','','individual','','Two articles we are much distressed for ; the one is bells, but the more important one is wood. Yet you cannot see wood for trees. No arrangement has been made, but by promises never performed, to supply the newcomers with fuel.','ltr_aba3449.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3450','letter','1801-05-03','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','William','Smith','','individual','','I have to acknowledge the receipt of the raspberry bushes, and the pot of strawberry vines, for which accept my thanks. I have had them placed in a good part of the garden','ltr_aba3450.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3451','letter','1801-07-12','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Adams','','individual','','You will find your father in his fields, attending to his hay-makers, and your mother busily occupied in the domestic concerns of her family.','ltr_aba3451.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3452','letter','1804-05-20','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','Had you been no other than the private inhabitant of Monticello, I should, ere this time, have addressed you with that sympathy which a recent event has awakened in my bosom ; but reasons of various kinds withheld my pen','ltr_aba3452.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3453','letter','1804-07-01','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','But you have been pleased to enter upon some subjects which call for a reply ; and as you observe that you have wished for an opportunity to express your sentiments, I have given them every weight they claim.','ltr_aba3453.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3454','letter','1804-08-18','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','Your statement inspecting Callender, and your motives for liberating him wear a different aspect as explained by you, from the impression which the act had made','ltr_aba3454.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3455','letter','1804-10-25','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','It was not until circumstances concurred to place you in the light of a rewarder and encourager of a libeller, whom you could not but detest and despise, that I withdrew the esteem I had long entertained for you.','ltr_aba3455.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3456','letter','1805-03-11','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','','Packard','','individual','','Scarcely had the grave closed over the remains of my esteemed friend Madam Sargent, relict of the late Judge, ere it was again opened to receive those of one still dearer to me.','ltr_aba3456.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3457','letter','1809-06-05','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','It is said, if riches increase, those increase that eat them ; but what shall we say, when the eaters increase without the wealth ?','ltr_aba3457.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3458','letter','1811-02-26','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Caroline','Smith','','individual','','I have some troubles in the loss of friends by death, and no small solicitude for the motherless offspring, but my trust and confidence are in that being who \"hears the young ravens when they cry.\"','ltr_aba3458.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3459','letter','1812-11-19','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Caroline','Smith','','individual','','Your neat, pretty letter, looking small, but containing much, reached me this day. I have a good mind to give you the journal of the day.','ltr_aba3459.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3460','letter','1814-02-03','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','F','Vanderkemp','','individual','','I agree with Mr. Vanderkemp, that, in declaring his opinion, he has expressed that of most gentlemen, the true cause of which I shall trace no farther than that they consider a companion more desirable than a rival.','ltr_aba3460.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3461','letter','1814-12-30','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','Elizabeth','Shaw','','individual','','With Mr. Gerry died one of the first and oldest patriots of the revolution a firm steady and unshaken friend of more than fifty years ripening. \"Such friends grow not thick on every bough.\"','ltr_aba3461.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aba3462','letter','1816-05-12','Quincy','MA','US','Abigail','Adams','','','Dexter','','individual','','How can I address you, or offer human consolation for a wound which must bleed afresh at every attempt to assuage it?','ltr_aba3462.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Letters of Mrs. Adams, The Wife of John Adams With an Introductory Memoir by Her Grandson, Charles Francis Adams, Volume II, 1840');
